article.description: — Tyler Stephenson-Moore's 28 points helped Stony Brook defeat North Carolina A&T 80-64 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Stephenson-Moore leads Stony Brook over North Carolina A&T 80-64
article.linkText: Stephenson-Moore leads Stony Brook over North Carolina A&T 80-64
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- — Tyler Stephenson-Moore's 28 points helped Stony Brook defeat North Carolina A&T 80-64 on Thursday night. Stephenson-Moore was 10-of-16 shooting, including 5 for 7 from 3-point range, and 3 for 4 from the free-throw line for the Seawolves (15-13, 8-7 Coastal Athletic Association). Andre Snoddy added 13 points and six rebounds. Jared Frey scored 11. Landon Glasper had 16 points and three steals to pace the Aggies (7-21, 5-10), who have lost six in a row. Nikolaos Chitikoudis scored 13 and Uchenna Kellman-Nicholes contributed 10 points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
